Program: Discovery
Title: Warm World - burying greenhouse gases
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxs8
Last Broadcast Date: 04 March 2001
Exploring the ways of storing greenhouse gases. Being able to keep greenhouse gases somewhere other than the atmosphere or aiding them to be absorbed them from the air - sequestration - could help combat climate change. Presenter: Toby Murcott.